The seventh Emir of Kontagora, Alhaji Muhammadu Barau Muazu, has commended the tireless efforts of security agents in Niger State, for ensuring normalcy and peace returned to his domain. He stated this at his palace in Kontagora, Kontagora Local Government Area of the state. He implored the people of the state to pray for the security agents in their continued fight against terrorism and armed banditry in the state. According to him, “It is mandatory for all to put hands on deck to build a better society.” On the just-concluded Eid-el-Fitr celebrations, Barau appealed to Muslim faithful to love and assist one another irrespective of religion, ethnic or tribal affiliation, adding that Islam teaches peace and unity, therefore, there is need for people to pray for their leaders. The monarch also urged the people to utilize the moral lessons learnt in the holy month of Ramadan, which he said include patience, endurance, feeling for others and protecting the dignity of one another.